# Newsletter Subscription System Features

## MVP Features (Must Have)
- [x] Basic subscription form for collecting email addresses
- [x] Email verification process with unique hash
- [x] Database storage for subscribers
- [x] Welcome email after verification
- [x] Queue system for sending emails
- [x] Prevent duplicate subscriptions
- [x] Basic validation for email format

## Important Features (Should Have)
- [ ] Unsubscribe functionality with one-click link
- [ ] Admin dashboard to view all subscribers
- [ ] Ability to manually add/remove subscribers
- [ ] Export subscribers list to CSV
- [ ] Basic analytics (subscription count, verification rate)
- [ ] Automatic linking of user accounts with same email as subscribers

## Enhanced Features (Nice to Have)
- [ ] Subscription preferences (content types, frequency)
- [ ] Segmentation of subscribers into groups/categories
- [ ] A/B testing for newsletter content
- [ ] Click tracking in sent emails
- [ ] Scheduled newsletter sending
- [ ] Templates for different types of newsletters
- [ ] Integration with popular email marketing services
- [ ] Double opt-in process for GDPR compliance
- [ ] Subscriber activity tracking

## Advanced Features (Future Expansion)
- [ ] Personalized content based on user preferences
- [ ] Automated re-engagement campaigns for inactive subscribers
- [ ] Integration with CRM systems
- [ ] Advanced analytics dashboard with conversion metrics
- [ ] Multi-language support for emails
- [ ] SMS notification option in addition to email
- [ ] API for third-party integrations
- [ ] Subscriber scoring based on engagement
- [ ] Automated content recommendations

## Registered Users and Subscription Integration
- [ ] Automatic subscription option during user registration
- [ ] Subscription management in user profile settings
- [ ] Sync verification status between user account and subscription
- [ ] Role-based access to newsletter content
- [ ] Special newsletter categories for registered users only
- [ ] Integration with notification preferences system
- [ ] Single sign-on for newsletter preference management